Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.88,0:10:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,so Tanyao tiles he hasn't discarded won't pass
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.28,0:11:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I absolutely can't deal into his hand
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.28,0:11:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They're playing damn dirty Mahjong
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.78,0:11:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.38,0:11:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,W-why?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.83,0:11:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,After that tile switch, what Harada's waiting on is tough to pin down
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.58,0:11:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than Pon that 9 Sou safe tile, wouldn't it be better to hold onto it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.84,0:11:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Holy shit
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.48,0:11:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't notice the swap?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.48,0:11:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't see Harada swap the tiles when changing seats!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.78,0:11:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.28,0:11:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Tanyao with 3 dora
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.28,0:11:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Mangan
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.01,0:11:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,How you figure that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.01,0:11:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Hunh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.84,0:11:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,How have you got 3 Dora?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.11,0:12:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,HE SWAPPED THE DORA
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.28,0:12:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,YOU FUUUUUUUU----
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.88,0:12:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Hell, swapping the dora indicator like that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.54,0:12:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,To imagine that in a mere instant...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.54,0:12:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That wasn't a conscious decision
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.54,0:12:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,My hands were moving on their own
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.98,0:12:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,In the midst of a game I seldom use my head
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.08,0:12:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,just my guts
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.83,0:12:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Follow them above all else
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.83,0:12:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Follow your gut instinct?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.83,0:12:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The only opportunity you have to follow chance is in THE NOW
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.53,0:12:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The feelings in your gut summon opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.13,0:12:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Cultivate them, raise them up
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.03,0:13:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The result:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.03,0:13:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll open the door to victory
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.04,0:13:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And THIS opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.34,0:13:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It WON'T escape us
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.48,0:13:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,From here on out
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.32,0:13:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The East team's counterattack begins!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.71,0:13:32.21,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(278.667,122)}East Team\NTen: 12000{\c&HFFFFFF&} Hiroyuki: 3000\NAkagi: 16000
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.71,0:13:32.21,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(815.111,122)}West Team\NHarada: 15000 Mitsui: 17000\NSoga: 25000 Akutsu: 11000
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.71,0:13:32.21,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1111.555,532.222)}Game 8\NEast Hand 3
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.85,0:13:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got a great hand
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.58,0:13:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,SanAnKou, Green Dragon and one Dora
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.58,0:13:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Even without declaring Riichi it's certainly a Mangan hand
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.75,0:14:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He drew a 4 Man
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.65,0:14:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll declare a closed Kan, I guess
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.58,0:14:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,H-he DIDN'T KAN!?!?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.45,0:14:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,W-why?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.85,0:14:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.95,0:14:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.18,0:14:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,A 2-5 wait?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.18,0:14:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that valuable SanAnKou just vanished!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.98,0:14:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got a Riichi, Green Dragon, 1 Dora hand
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.35,0:14:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,6,400 points at most
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.35,0:14:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,WHY?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.28,0:14:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I see what's going on
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.35,0:14:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Harada's playing defensively
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.15,0:14:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,playing consecutive safe tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.15,0:14:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The West team won't deal into his hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.15,0:15:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got an impossible winning tile
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.05,0:15:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He can't possibly draw a 2/5 Man
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.75,0:15:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.52,0:15:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.78,0:15:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But Akagi's wait is most probably low Man tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.78,0:15:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no reason why he should discard that tile!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.35,0:15:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got a safe North Wind tile, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.78,0:16:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got a dora and kan-dora in my hand
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.28,0:16:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If I draw the North Wind I've got a Haneman hand
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.85,0:16:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It shouldn't be any problem...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.68,0:16:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,if I discard a lower Sou tile
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.18,0:16:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.08,0:16:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Too bad
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.95,0:16:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's it
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.48,0:16:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,No Ura-dora
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.58,0:16:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only a Mangan hand
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.35,0:16:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He changed his wait AFTER declaring riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.25,0:16:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So he couldn't declare Kan
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.25,0:16:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, using an ILLEGAL Kan
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.25,0:16:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He scalped Harada!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.58,0:17:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It was difficult to notice from the West team's perspective
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.58,0:17:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,while the tile he actually drew was hidden in his palm
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.95,0:17:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,he returned the tile he could actually Kan with to his hand
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.78,0:17:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So there was unmistakably 4 tiles to Kan in his hand
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.35,0:17:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,With movements so fluid
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.58,0:17:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It looked like there was nothing amiss
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.08,0:17:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And with this *illegal Kan
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.08,0:17:25.93,Default - top - cyan,,0,0,0,,*Illegal Kan: Players may only Kan when drawing the tile that completes their set of 4. Here Akagi used slight of hand to Kan when he drew an unrelated tile. This also breaks the separate rule which does not allow changing waits after delaring Riichi. lmfao
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.38,0:17:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,from a 2-5 Man wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.18,0:17:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,he instantly went to a 1 Sou single tile wait
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.45,0:17:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of there were already two 2 Sou tiles in the discards...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.25,0:17:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Harada couldn't dodge this 1 Sou wait
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.25,0:17:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,CAMOUFLAGE is what you do before you delcare Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.95,0:17:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a Mahjong PREREQUISITE
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.62,0:17:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi turned that requirement itself on its head
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.95,0:17:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,an upset itself in disguise
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.95,0:17:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,A 1 Sou single tile wait!
